<lyrics>[V1]
 Oh Lord my God!
 When I in awesome wonder,
 Consider all the worlds
 Thy hands have made;
 I see the stars,
 I hear the rolling thunder,
 Thy pow'r throughout
 The universe displayed.

[V2]
 CHORUS
 Then sings my soul,
 My Saviour God to Thee;
 How great Thou art,
 How great Thou art!
 Then sings my soul,
 My Saviour God to Thee;
 How great Thou art,
 How great Thou art!

[V3]
 When through the woods,
 And forest glades I wander
 And hear the birds,
 Sing sweetly in the trees;
 When I look down,
 From lofty mountain grandeur
 And hear the brook
 And feel the gentle breeze.

[V4]
 And when I think that God,
 His Son not sparing,
 Sent Him to die,
 I scarce can take it in;
 That on the cross,
 My burden gladly bearing,
 He bled and died,
 To take away my sin.

[V5]
 When Christ shall come,
 With shout of acclamation
 And take me home,
 What joy shall fill my heart!
 Then I shall bow,
 In humble adoration
 And there proclaim,
 My God, how great
 Thou art!</lyrics>
<title>How great thou art, Korversion</title>
</song>